data.content:
Three EF Core 10 breaking changes hit your code:

---

### 1. `ExecuteUpdateAsync` — now takes a regular lambda, not an expression tree

Your entire expression-tree construction can be replaced with simple imperative code:

```csharp
// .NET 10 — just use a lambda with conditionals
await context.Blogs.ExecuteUpdateAsync(s =>
{
    s.SetProperty(b => b.Views, 8);
    if (nameChanged)
    {
        s.SetProperty(b => b.Name, "foo");
    }
});
```

Delete all the `Expression.Parameter` / `Expression.Lambda` / `Expression.Call` machinery.

---

### 2. Complex type column names — two changes

**a) Sibling uniquification:** Since both `ShippingAddress` and `BillingAddress` have a `Street` property, EF 10 auto-uniquifies the column names (e.g., appending a number). This generates a migration renaming columns.

**b) Nested full-path naming:** `Order.Payment.BillingAddress.City` was previously mapped to `BillingAddress_City`; it's now `Payment_BillingAddress_City`.

**Fix:** Pin the old names explicitly:

```csharp
modelBuilder.Entity<Customer>(b =>
{
    b.ComplexProperty(c => c.ShippingAddress, sa =>
    {
        sa.Property(a => a.Street).HasColumnName("ShippingAddress_Street");
        // … other properties
    });
    b.ComplexProperty(c => c.BillingAddress, ba =>
    {
        ba.Property(a => a.Street).HasColumnName("BillingAddress_Street");
    });
});

// For nested complex types:
modelBuilder.Entity<Order>(b =>
{
    b.ComplexProperty(o => o.Payment, p =>
    {
        p.ComplexProperty(pay => pay.BillingAddress, ba =>
        {
            ba.Property(a => a.City).HasColumnName("BillingAddress_City");
        });
    });
});
```

Or generate a new migration and accept the renames — but that requires a coordinated deployment.

---

### 3. `IRelationalCommandDiagnosticsLogger` — new `logCommandText` parameter

Every method gained a `string logCommandText` parameter at the end:

```csharp
public class MyLogger : IRelationalCommandDiagnosticsLogger
{
    public InterceptionResult<DbDataReader> CommandReaderExecuting(
        IRelationalConnection connection,
        DbCommand command,
        DbContext context,
        Guid commandId,
        Guid connectionId,
        DateTimeOffset startTime,
        string logCommandText)   // ← add this
    {
        // logCommandText = redacted SQL safe for logging
        // command.CommandText = actual SQL
    }
}
```

Add the parameter to **every** method in the interface (`CommandReaderExecuted`, `CommandScalarExecuting`, etc.) — they all changed the same way.
